text: [Music]
greetings my name is Matt Wood and I'm
here at the AWS headquarters in Seattle
to tell you about two new features we
just added to Amazon S3 you guys know S3
number one is a life cycle policy to
expire incomplete multi-part uploads
multi-part uploads allow you to take
large files split them up and upload
those parts into parallel so that you
can get those objects uploaded more
quickly the second is the ability to be
able to set life cycle policy on delete
markers for expired objects S3 allows
you to set up versioning for objects so
that you not only have the current
version available but all previous
versions available for an object and
when you delete that object S3 inserts
what we call a delete marker into the
version history so that it knows that
the object has been deleted but the
previous versions are still available
however when those previous versions are
expired or removed from S3 you can end
up with a single delete marker stored in
in S3 and that can slow down the
operations of listing the objects in a
bucket so today you can add a simple
policy to remove those delete markers on
expired objects and increase the
performance of list operations for very
large numbers of objects inside buckets
that's it thank you very

much
